stylometry: The tradeoff you must balance when deciding how much inventory to order is demand and costs.  If you order to much inventory you are going to have extra holding costs when the product sits in your factory.  This is a problem especially if the product is food or things that spoil over time.  If you dont order enough inventory you are not going to satisfy demand and will therefore have to order more products and quick shipments times will eat into your profits.  There are also sometimes production costs associated with the inventory you order.  The goal of businesses is to try and figure out how much inventory to order based on the demand and costs that are associated with order and setting up the product in order to be able to sell it.  EOQ is the most basic inventory model and it equalizes the ability of the company to order the amount of inventory necessary to satisfy and meet demand.
